SLS 26RS-837 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 25
BY SENATOR WHEAT
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates Tuesday, March 17, 2026, as Louisiana
Society of Professional Surveyors Day at the Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate March 17, 2026, as Louisiana Professional Surveyors Day at the Louisiana
3 State Capitol and to recognize National Surveyors Week, which honors the Louisiana
4 Society of Professional Surveyors for its contributions in protecting property rights,
5 supporting economic development, and promoting the land surveying profession in
6 Louisiana.
7 WHEREAS, land surveying is among the oldest and most foundational professions
8 in the United States, providing the measurements and boundaries upon which property
9 ownership, infrastructure, and communities are built; and
10 WHEREAS, as the United States commemorates the 250th anniversary of the signing
11 of the Declaration of Independence in 2026, it is appropriate to recognize that land surveying
12 played a critical role in the development and expansion of the nation; and
13 WHEREAS, many early American leaders who helped shape the nation were also
14 land surveyors, including George Washington, Thomas Jefferson, and Abraham Lincoln, and
15 it was the surveying work of those early American leaders that contributed to the orderly
16 division of land, the establishment of property rights, and the development of communities
17 across the expanding United States; and
18 WHEREAS, the principles of accurate measurement and defined property boundaries
