1 established by early surveyors helped lay the legal and economic framework that supported,
2 and continues to support, private property rights and economic growth throughout the nation;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, in the state of Louisiana, professional land surveyors provide essential
5 services that support transportation infrastructure, public works, residential and commercial
6 development, flood protection systems, and critical energy and industrial facilities that help
7 drive the state's economy; and
8 WHEREAS, professional land surveyors play a vital role in coastal restoration and
9 protection efforts, assisting with mapping, elevation data, and land boundary determinations
10 necessary for major projects that safeguard Louisiana's coast; and
11 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Society of Professional Surveyors represents professional
12 land surveyors across the state and is dedicated to advancing the profession through
13 education, professional standards, public outreach, and legislative advocacy; and
14 WHEREAS, National Surveyors Week, observed each year in March, highlights the
15 important work performed by professional land surveyors and recognizes their contributions
16 to communities and economic development across the country.
17 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
18 does hereby designate March 17, 2026, as Louisiana Professional Surveyors Day at the
19 Louisiana State Capitol and does hereby commend the Louisiana Society of Professional
20 Surveyors for its dedication to protecting property rights, advancing professional standards,
21 and supporting the growth and development of Louisiana.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
23 Louisiana Society of Professional Surveyors.
